-- Hong Kong Stocks Fall for Second Day Before China Data
-- B y   E l e n i   H i m a r a s
-- 2013-04-15T01:37:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-15/hong-kong-stocks-fall-for-second-day-before-china-data-correct-.html
(Corrects to show second day of decline in lead.)  Hong Kong stocks fell for a second
day ahead of an announcement on Chinese economic growth.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  dropped 0.8 percent to 21,928.39 as of
9:34 a.m. in Hong Kong. The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index,
which tracks mainland shares, dropped 1.1 percent to 10,542.63.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eleni Himaras in Hong Kong at 
 ehimaras@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
